    "creation_date" : 1298566384,
    "answer_id" : 5107805,
    "question_id" : 493494,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>I needed the absolute value of a long , and looked deeply into Math.abs and found that if my argument is less than LONG.MIN_VAL which is -9223372036854775808l, then the abs function would not return an absolute value but only the minimum value. Inthis case if your code is using this abs value further then there might be an issue.</p>\n"
  }, {
