    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you're interested in the mechanics of two's complement, here's the absolutely inefficient, but illustrative low-level way this is made:</p>\n\n<pre><code>private static int makeAbsolute(int number){\n     if(number &gt;=0){\n        return number;\n     } else{\n        return (~number)+1;\n     }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 184519,
      "reputation" : 23432,
      "user_id" : 420613,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 87,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/7Ai0g.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Muhammad Imran Tariq",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/420613/muhammad-imran-tariq"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
