    "answer_id" : 56476372,
    "question_id" : 493494,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Library function <code>Math.abs()</code> can be used.<br>\n<code>Math.abs()</code> returns the absolute value of the argument  </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <ul>\n  <li>if the argument is negative, it returns the negation of the argument.  </li>\n  <li>if the argument is positive, it returns the number as it is.  </li>\n  </ul>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>e.g:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><code>int x=-5;</code><br>\n<code>System.out.println(Math.abs(x));</code></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Output: 5</p>\n\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li><code>int y=6;</code><br>\n<code>System.out.println(Math.abs(y));</code></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Output: 6</p>\n"
  }, {
