    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>To convert negative number to positive number (this is called absolute value), uses Math.abs(). This Math.abs() method is work like this</p>\n<p><code>“number = (number &lt; 0 ? -number : number);&quot;.</code></p>\n<p><strong>In below example, <code>Math.abs(-1)</code> will convert the negative number 1 to positive 1.</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>example</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>public static void main(String[] args) {</p>\n<pre><code>    int total = 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + (-1);\n    \n    //output 3\n    System.out.println(&quot;Total : &quot; + total);\n    \n    int total2 = 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + Math.abs(-1);\n    \n    //output 5\n    System.out.println(&quot;Total 2 (absolute value) : &quot; + total2);\n    \n}\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em><strong>Output</strong></em></p>\n<p>Total : 3\nTotal 2 (absolute value) : 5</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
  }, {
