    "question_id" : 493494,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I see people are saying that <code>Math.abs(number)</code> but this method is not full proof.</p>\n<p>This fails when you try to wrap <code>Math.abs(Integer.MIN_VALUE)</code> (see ref. <a href=\"https://youtu.be/IWrpDP-ad7g\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://youtu.be/IWrpDP-ad7g</a>)</p>\n<p>If you are not sure whether you are going to receive the <code>Integer.MIN_VALUE</code> in the input. It is always recommended to check for that number and handle it manually.</p>\n"
